<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,605,791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,293,605,631]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[315,486,605,630]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Buchananiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,486,605,630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Buchananiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other genera of the tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1224,605,631]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dufouriellini">Dufouriellini</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: rostrum short, almost reaching fore coxae; pronotum strongly narrowed anteriorly, depressed posteromedially, and with a swollen callus and deeply concave posterior margin; collar distinct; ostiolar peritreme posteriorly curved and extending to the anterior margin of the metapleuron; a medioventral opening of the omphalus usually present on sternum VII.
</paragraph>
